    }


3. Exposed API via Amazon API Gateway 
   - Created REST API  
   - Created a method (POST)  
   - Integrated with my Lambda function  
   - Enabled CORS for frontend calls  

4. Amazon DynamoDB as Database   
   - Created a table to store calculation history (result, timestamp)  
   - Lambda writes each result to DynamoDB  

5. Managed Permissions with AWS IAM  
   - Created IAM role for Lambda execution  
   - Attached inline policy granting:  
        "dynamodb:PutItem",
        "dynamodb:DeleteItem",
        "dynamodb:GetItem",
        "dynamodb:Scan",
        "dynamodb:Query",
        "dynamodb:UpdateItem"  
   - Ensured least-privilege access (only necessary DynamoDB actions)


7. Deploy & Test
   - Amplify handled frontend deployment.
   - Tested web app and works excellently.  

THANKS FOR FOLLOWING!!! :-) 
